                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " THE HORIZONTAL BEAM-TUBE HB11, WHICH HAS A SYS-",
                " TEM OF FOCUSING NEUTRON MIRRORS NEAR THE REACTOR CORE,",
                " WAS USED. TRANSMISSION OF NEUTRONS CAN ONLY TAKE PLACE",
                " BY TOTAL REFLECTION AT THE NICKEL MIRROR SURFACES,",
                " WHICH THUS ACT AS A LOW-PASS NEUTRON FILTER. THE 6 CM",
                " DIAMETER NEUTRON BEAM WAS SHAPED WITH AN ADDITIONAL",
                " BORON PLASTIC AND LIF DIAPHRAGM NEAR THE TARGET."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE NEUTRON SPECTRUM EAS DETERMINED BY IRRADIATING TWO",
                " STACKS OF TWENTY 400 MG/CM2 THICK 2.5 X 2.5 CM2 GOLD",
                " FOILS, ONE BEFORE AND ONE AFTER THE TARGET GAS CELL."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " THE 20.5 MEV CAPTURE GAMMA RAYS WERE DETECTED",
                " BY TWO 25 CM DIAMETER BY 25 CM LONG NAI-TL DETECTORS,",
                " BOTH PLACED 32.6 CM FROM THE TARGET CELL AND AT 90",
                " DEGREES WITH RESPECT TO THE NEUTRON BEAM. THE DETEC-",
                " TORS WERE SHIELDED AGAINST SCATTERED NEUTRONS AND",
                " GAMMA-RAYS NOT ORIGINATING FROM THE TARGET. THE RES-",
                " PONSE FUNCTION WAS CALCULATED WITH A MONTE CARLO CODE."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE TARGET CELL CONSISTED OF AN ALUMINUM CYLINDRICAL",
